<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Harsh" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Harsh,</orth> 1) rugged to the touch, rough: <cit><quote>to whose soft seizure the cygnet's down is h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 58</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) grating on the ear: <cit><quote>h. in voice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 134" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 134</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>too h. a descant,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 94</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.208" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.940" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 940</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.312" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 312</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.97" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 97</bibl>.
<lb />3) bitter and disagreeable to the taste: <cit><quote>sweet revenge grows h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 116</bibl></cit>.
<lb />4) rough, rude, repulsive: <cit><quote>h., featureless and rude,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 11.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 11, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this h. indignity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.289" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 289</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. Jew,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 123</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>tedious it were to tell and h. to hear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 107</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 183</bibl>. <cit><quote>a most h. language,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.198" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 198</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy h. rude tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. rage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 183</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so h., so blunt, unnatural,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 1, 86</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>too h. a style,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.360" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 360</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this h. world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.359" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 359</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. conference,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. fortune,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.6.54" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that h., noble, simple nothing, that Cloten,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 135</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy h. and potent injuries,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.83" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 83</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>